<item>
            <title>[FLINK-4652] Don&apos;t pass credentials explicitly to AmazonClient - use credentials provider instead</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-4652</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;By using the credentials explicitly we are responsible for checking and refreshing credentials before they expire. If no refreshment is done we will encounter AmazonServiceException: &apos;The security token included in the request is expired&apos;. To utilize automatic refreshment of credentials pass the AWSCredentialsProvider direclty to AmazonClient by removing the getCredentials() call.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
