                            <comment id="15575336" author="githubbot" created="Fri, 14 Oct 2016 13:29:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;GitHub user greghogan opened a pull request:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/2635&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/2635&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-4652&quot; title=&quot;Don&amp;#39;t pass credentials explicitly to AmazonClient - use credentials provider instead&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FLINK-4652&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FLINK-4652&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;streaming connectors&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; Automatically refresh AWS credentials&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    By using the credentials explicitly we are responsible for checking and refreshing credentials before they expire. If no refreshment is done we will encounter AmazonServiceException: &apos;The security token included in the request is expired&apos;. Utilize automatic refreshment of credentials by passing the AWSCredentialsProvider directly to AmazonClient by removing the getCredentials() call.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;You can merge this pull request into a Git repository by running:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    $ git pull &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/greghogan/flink&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/greghogan/flink&lt;/a&gt; 4652_dont_pass_credentials_explicitly_to_amazonclient&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Alternatively you can review and apply these changes as the patch at:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/2635.patch&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/flink/pull/2635.patch&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To close this pull request, make a commit to your master/trunk branch&lt;br/&gt;
with (at least) the following in the commit message:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    This closes #2635&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;commit 7958e6e595ff9a1e9b83c4e8fa9b4a69a3427d3f&lt;br/&gt;
Author: Greg Hogan &amp;lt;code@greghogan.com&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Date:   2016-10-14T13:24:14Z&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-4652&quot; title=&quot;Don&amp;#39;t pass credentials explicitly to AmazonClient - use credentials provider instead&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;FLINK-4652&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;FLINK-4652&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;streaming connectors&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; Automatically refresh AWS credentials&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;    By using the credentials explicitly we are responsible for checking and&lt;br/&gt;
    refreshing credentials before they expire. If no refreshment is done we&lt;br/&gt;
    will encounter AmazonServiceException: &apos;The security token included in&lt;br/&gt;
    the request is expired&apos;. Utilize automatic refreshment of credentials&lt;br/&gt;
    by passing the AWSCredentialsProvider directly to AmazonClient by removing&lt;br/&gt;
    the getCredentials() call.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;</comment>
